  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The new shopfront, by reason of the size and position of the fasica;, the insertion of an incongruous aluminium frame and recessed position  of the glazing results in the loss of traditional elements within this shopfront and a change of proportions which is detrimental to the historic visual appearance and character of the host building, street scene and the wider Duncan Terrace/ Colebrooke Row Conservation Area. The new shopfront is therefore contrary to Policies CS 9 (Protecting and enhancing Islington's built and historic environment) of the Core Strategy 2011,  D4 (Designing in Context), D11 (Alterations and Extensions), D13 (Shopfronts), D22 (New Development), and D24 (Materials) of Islington Council's Unitary Development Plan (2002), Islington's Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002), Islington Shopfront Design Guide and Planning Policy Statement 5: Planning for the Historic Environment."
